@bashtage I would agree that improved docstring would help, but I would argue that making `convert_numeric=True` different from `convert_numeric="coerce"` would fix this specific problem. This is similar to how the convert_dates argument works.

With `convert_numeric=True`, conversion would only occur if every value in a field conforms to an <i>integer-like</i> value. `convert_numeric="coerce"` would be the same as `convert_numeric=True` is currently.

@jreback sounds like a fun thing to work on this weekend!
